# Migration to Acuris

## Endpoint cross-reference

| Vendor function                                 | Acuris SDK                                |
| ----------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| Informatica AddressDoctor `AD_VerifyAddress`    | `validateAddress`                         |
| Informatica AddressDoctor `AD_Search`           | `suggestAddress` + `validateAddress`      |
| Informatica AddressDoctor `AD_Geocode`          | `geocodeAddress`                          |
| Loqate `Capture/Find` + `Retrieve`              | `suggestAddress` + `validateAddress`      |
| Loqate `Verify`                                 | `validateAddress`                         |
| Experian QAS / Aperture `Search` + `Format`     | `validateAddress` (single round-trip)     |
| Experian QAS `Suggestions`                      | `suggestAddress`                          |
| Melissa Personator `Verify`                     | `validateAddress`                         |
| Melissa Global Address Verification             | `validateAddress`                         |
| Melissa ExpressEntry                            | `suggestAddress`                          |
| Smarty US Street API                            | `validateAddress` (`country: "usa"`)      |
| Smarty US Autocomplete Pro API                  | `suggestAddress` (`country: "usa"`)       |
| Smarty International Street API                 | `validateAddress` (ISO-3 lowercase)       |
| Smarty US Reverse Geo API                       | `reverseGeocode` (`country: "usa"`)       |

## Status-code mapping

`accuracy_type` (Acuris) + `confidence` collapse the vendor-specific
status hierarchies:

| Generic bucket          | Vendor equivalent                                      | Acuris condition                                       |
| ----------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| Verified to premise     | QAS `V`, Loqate `V5`, Melissa `AV25`, Smarty `Rooftop` | `accuracy_type ∈ {rooftop, parcel}` AND `confidence ≥ 0.9` |
| Verified to street      | QAS `P`, Loqate `V4`, Melissa `AV24`, Smarty `Zip9`    | `accuracy_type ∈ {street_interpolated, street_center}` |
| Verified to locality    | QAS `R`, Melissa `AV23`                                | `accuracy_type ∈ {postcode, locality, locality_centroid}` |
| No / weak match         | QAS `U`, Loqate `V1`, Melissa `AV12`, Smarty `Unknown` | `accuracy_type === null` or `confidence < 0.4`         |
| Component corrected     | All vendors flag this distinctly                       | `input_corrected === true`                             |

## Country code normalization

| Vendor format          | Convert to Acuris ISO-3 lowercase           |
| ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| ISO-2 (`"US"`, `"DE"`) | `iso2 → iso3, lowercase` (`"us" → "usa"`)   |
| ISO-3 uppercase        | `.toLowerCase()`                            |
| Full name              | Lookup table → ISO-3 lowercase              |

## What doesn't migrate

- **CASS / SERP / DPV / SuiteLink / LACSLink certifications** —
  USPS / postal-authority certifications. Acuris is rooftop-grade
  but not certified against these schemes. If the customer needs
  presort discounts, this migration alone won't suffice.
- **Vendor-specific stable IDs** (Melissa MAK, Loqate Container,
  Experian `global_address_key`). Acuris doesn't assign per-address
  IDs. Switch downstream dedupe to a hash of
  `(country, standardized.formatted_address)`.
- **Name / email / phone enrichment** (Personator extras, QAS
  Authenticate). Acuris is address-only.

